<subSubSection id="48D355CA8E66FFE848F75564FD3EFD57" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="007606418E66FFE848F75564FD3EFD57" blockId="40.[151,1437,151,680]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E66FFE848F75564FE9EFD90" bold="true" box="[199,315,584,608]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Remarks.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus id="DF72B8E38E66FFE84944556BFE73FDAF" box="[372,470,583,607]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28E66FFE849CA5564FD2EFD90" authorityName="Olmi" authorityYear="2010" box="[506,651,584,608]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Aphelopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wushensis">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E66FFE849CA5564FD2EFD90" box="[506,651,584,608]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">A. wushensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the male erroneously identified as 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28E66FFE84C1B5564FAF2FDAF" authority="Olmi, 1984" authorityName="Olmi" authorityYear="1984" box="[1067,1367,583,608]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Aphelopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="penanganus">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E66FFE84C1B5564FB74FD90" box="[1067,1233,584,608]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">A. penanganus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="64587BB08E66FFE84CE7556BFAF2FDAF" author="Olmi" box="[1239,1367,583,607]" firstAuthor="Olmi" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" pagination="1 - 1913" refId="ref364993" refString="Olmi, M. (1984) A revision of the Dryinidae (Hymenoptera). Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 37, I - XII + 1 - 1913." type="journal article" year="1984">
Olmi, 
<quantity id="C731ABA48E66FFE84D2F556BFAD6FDAF" box="[1311,1395,583,607]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.03936" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" unit="in" value="1984.0">
<quantity id="C731ABA48E66FFE84D2F556BFAF2FDAF" box="[1311,1367,583,607]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.03936" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" unit="in" value="1984.0">1984</quantity>
in
</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
the key to the males of 
<collectingRegion id="C20DC8A38E66FFE849495540FE70FD74" box="[377,469,620,644]" country="Democratic Republic of the Congo" name="Orientale" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Oriental</collectingRegion>
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28E66FFE849ED5540FDF6FD74" authorityName="Dalman" authorityYear="1823" box="[477,595,620,644]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Aphelopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E66FFE849ED5540FDF6FD74" box="[477,595,620,644]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Aphelopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
presented by 
<bibRefCitation id="64587BB08E66FFE84AC45540FC1FFD74" author="Xu, Z. &amp; He, J." box="[756,954,620,644]" journalOrPublisher="Entomotaxonomia" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" pagination="128" part="21" refId="ref372190" refString="Xu, Z. &amp; He, J. (1999 a) Seven new recorded species of Dryinidae (Hymenoptera) from China. Entomotaxonomia, 21 (2), 128." title="Seven new recorded species of Dryinidae (Hymenoptera) from China" type="journal article" year="1999">
Xu 
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E66FFE84B2E5541FCFDFD74" box="[798,856,620,644]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">et al.</emphasis>
(1999a)
</bibRefCitation>
. Really, the true male of 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28E66FFE84CE95540FA24FD74" authorityName="Olmi" authorityYear="1984" box="[1241,1409,620,644]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Aphelopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="penanganus">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E66FFE84CE95540FA24FD74" box="[1241,1409,620,644]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">A. penanganus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is that described as 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28E66FFE8496855BCFE14FD58" authorityName="He &amp; Xu" authorityYear="2002" box="[344,433,656,680]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Aphelopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="olmii">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E66FFE8496855BCFE14FD58" box="[344,433,656,680]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">A. olmii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="64587BB08E66FFE849EB55BCFD33FD57" author="He &amp; Xu" box="[475,662,655,679]" firstAuthor="He" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" refId="ref360566" refString="He, J. &amp; Xu, Z. (2002) Hymenoptera Dryinidae. Fauna Sinica, 29. Science Press, Beijing, China, 464 pp." type="book" year="2002">He &amp; Xu (2002)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
